<!DOCTYPE html
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>ELH - Java example</title>
    <body>
        <h1>ELH <$ foo="test" $> example</h1>
        <p>Runs the following code on the server, similar to PHP <$ echo "$foo" $></p>
        <pre>
            <code>
                public static void main(String[] args) {
                    System.out.println("&lt;p&gt;");
                    for (int num = 100, i = 1; num <= 1000; num++) {
                        if (num % 5 == 0 && num % 6 == 0) { 
                            String whiteSpace = (i % 10 == 0) ? "&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;" : "  ";
                            System.out.printf("%d%s", num, whiteSpace);
                            i++;
                        }
                    }
                    System.out.println("&lt;/p&gt;");
                }
            </code>
        </pre>
        <p>The output:</p>
        <$java
            public static void main(String[] args) {
                System.out.println("<p>");
                for (int num = 100, i = 1; num <= 1000; num++) {
                    if (num % 5 == 0 && num % 6 == 0) { 
                        String whiteSpace = (i % 10 == 0) ? "</p><p>" : "  ";
                        System.out.printf("%d%s", num, whiteSpace);
                        i++;
                    }
                }
                System.out.println("</p>");
            }
        $>
    </body>
</html>
